Eden Hazard was substituted with 28 minutes to go in Belgium's 1-0 win over Israel on Tuesday . 
  The Chelsea playmaker has played 48 games this season for club and country . 
  Belgium manager Marc Wilmots said he felt Hazard was tired after the game . 
  Vincent Kompany was sent off within two minutes of Hazard being substituted . 
  Hazard has admitted an intense campaign with Chelsea may have left him too tired . 
  The 24-year-old has played all but five of Chelsea's games . 
 